repository-code: "https://github.com/0thernes/black-hole-simulation-lab"
abstract: >-
  A research-first, C++20 general-relativity black-hole simulation lab:
  a Carter-separated Kerr null-geodesic engine, closed-form Bardeen
  shadow rendering, a verification-oracle test discipline, black-hole
  thermodynamics, and a quasinormal-mode module (Leaver continued-fraction
  solver for Schwarzschild and Kerr, WKB cross-check, and a spectroscopy
  front-end realizing the no-hair consistency test). Every published value
  carries an explicit scientific truth tier. AI-assisted, human-directed and
  human-reviewed; physics validated against independent published references.
keywords:
  - general relativity
  - black holes
  - Kerr metric
  - quasinormal modes
  - black-hole spectroscopy
  - no-hair theorem
  - numerical relativity
  - AI-assisted research
